[{"id":"VR876703","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a black horizontal rectangle containing nine white ovals spaced equidistantly in a straight line. The fifth oval is labeled Central Maximum. Two dashed vertical lines are drawn from the sixth and ninth oval and the space between these lines is labeled 4.50 times 10 raised to the negative 2 power, meters.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876703.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A double slit with a slit spacing of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5.00 times 10 raised to the negative 5 power meters\"><math alttext=\"5.00 times 10 raised to the negative 5 power meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5.00</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span> is used to determine the wavelength of a laser. When the laser is shined onto the double slit, the pattern shown in the figure is produced on a screen <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.500 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.500 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.500</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span> from the double slit. The first and fourth bright spots to the right of the central bright maximum are separated by a distance of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4.50 times 10 raised to the negative 2 power, meters\"><math alttext=\"4.50 times 10 raised to the negative 2 power, meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>4.50</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span>, as indicated. What is the wavelength of the laser?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876703_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.67 times 10 raised to the negative 9 power, meters\"><math alttext=\"1.67 times 10 raised to the negative 9 power, meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1.67</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.50 times 10 raised to the negative 6 power, meters\"><math alttext=\"1.50 times 10 raised to the negative 6 power, meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1.50</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.67 times 10 raised to the negative 5 power, meters\"><math alttext=\"1.67 times 10 raised to the negative 5 power, meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1.67</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.50 times 10 raised to the negative 2 power, meters\"><math alttext=\"1.50 times 10 raised to the negative 2 power, meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>1.50</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]